    "5.Selection: This stage involves choosing parent chromosomes from a population to breed a new generation.",
    "A widely utilized method for selection is tournament selection, where two chromosomes are randomly chosen, and the one with a higher fitness score is selected as a parent.",
    "This process ensures that individuals with better solutions are more likely to pass on their characteristics.6.",
    "Crossover: Crossover is the operator applied to the chosen parents to generate the new children.",
    "In this research, the crossover mechanism randomly decides for each gene whether to take it from the first or second parent, promoting diversity and combining beneficial traits.7."
  ],
